The space
Casa de Paz (House of Peace) is like staying with family! If you want to experience San Francisco
like a local...instead of feeling like a tourist, this is the place for you.
Here you will wake up in your own peaceful room, with a view of San Francisco & the smell of fresh coffee brewing downstairs!

You may also enjoy the following amenities:
Use of kitchen
Internet/cable
Laundry Facilities
Beautiful Hiking right outside the back door! (Also, walking distance from the 49er stadium if you're a football fan!)
Less than 1 &1/2 blocks from public transportation (T-line light rail)
Minutes away from all main freeways, provides a quick commute

name: Room downtown one person
description:
I am subletting my room, only reservations for at least 60 days are considered. Room for 1 person, only one guest (you) since the lease will include you and me, no overnight visitors, management monitors access. Shower bathroom on hallway

The space
Single room in Down Town San Francisco.
Old style residential hotel, near everything.

At least 2+ months reservation Only.

Conveniently located, close to everything in the city.
Stays from 3 months only.

Room with a sink and some cooking things. Bath and restroom on hall way, never crowded.

I am subletting and you would be included in lease as a second and only other guest. They enforce entrance of tenants after 9 pm
so this reservation is for 1 more person Only,


Location: near,
CIVIC CENTER, UNION SQUARE, SOMA, CASTRO, EMBARCADERO, MISSION.
1/2 a block from Bart (subway),
5 min. walk to Union Square,
15 min walk to Ca
neighborhood_overview: Downtown.... right between the run down area and the new mid-market and SOMA, very safe around here but you definitely will see homeless people
host_about:
I am a long-time language instructor. and translator. So, I am knowledgeable and love to share the Latino language and Cultures. It also helps that I like walking around the city, 

Other personal likes: a nice cup a tea mainly outdoors, etc.  I have practiced Yoga for over 30 years and Tai-chi, too

I am well aware of current events and news -real news-

Ok, nos vemos amigous

name: Cool Timeshare/Hotel (Union Sq.)
description:
The Donatello is a timeshare/hotel which is one of the top hotels in San Francisco. Just show up and check in like any other hotel, no arranging to get keys necessary.

- 1 KING BED and 1 QUEEN SLEEPER SOFA
- Parking: $32 per night

The space
DESCRIPTION
With 400 square feet of space and 10 foot ceilings, these rooms are some of the largest in the San Francisco area. Rooms are elegant and provide many of the luxuries of home including wet-bar and sink, compact refrigerator and microwave, sofa sleeper, cd player and in-room safe. All rooms have one KING BED and one QUEEN SLEEPER SOFA and sleep maximum of 4 people. No rollaways are available.

Services & Amenities:
Spacious studio accommodations
24-hour front desk
Concierge services
Intimate Italian dining at Zingari Ristorante
Indoor valet parking ($32 per night, unlimited in and out privileges)
Meeting facilities
Dry cleaning services (fee)
Roo
neighborhood_overview: Lunch at the Rotunda Restaurant in Nieman Marcus.  Great food and great view of Union Square!
host_about:
At this point in my life, my only hobbies are whatever I am doing with my amazing young daughters.  Some may call it boring. I call it joy.

I am a timeshare owner who loves to travel. Timeshares (resale, NEVER EVER direct from developer NO MATTER WHAT) have immeasurably enhanced my family's travel lifestyle.
